Time when you took lead on a project and drove impact, manage it end to end or promote collaboration on a particular project? Time when you managed up/lead?
How have you leveraged data to develop a strategy? Or How do you get people to agree with your point of view? What metrics do you use to drive positive change?
Describe a past conflict with a co-worker and how did you resolve?
Give me an example of when you received criticism or Tell me about a time you disagreed with feedback you received. How did you address it?
Describe a time you took the lead on a project Or What did you do when you needed to motivate a group of individuals or promote collaboration on a particular project?

S Owning a datacenter deployment product and driving impact through improving success rate of the turn up procedure and reducing the time required to make the network operational
T Task was analyse the product and create datapoints to which steps/dependencies are talking the most time/are failing a lot, for example config push, switch build (owned by onsite team)
FW provisioning (owned by the FW team). What I found through data points were the average and p90 duration for which the workflow stays with the external teams specifically FW team was a lot > 60 days which including steps like HW vetting, OS staging, protocol enablement, traffic testing
A I took the lead and created a weekly forum with FW managers and senior engineers to drive improvement in the overall process, initially we had conflicts of interest because
  they did not agree that they were bottleneck, after presenting the data and proving my point  I came up with a tactical plan to improve the process namely:
   - Our WF use to fail if FWs had ongoing patching, created a locking mechanism to avoid dispatching our campaign until the reservation is lifted and vice versa.
   - prioritise racks belonging to the same datacenter compared to multiple datacenter as that would expedite the process
   - prioritise greenfield projects as they had more visibilty
   - onboarding traffic testing to networking instead of firewall team as we already had the underlying infrastructure for it
R Result was we see improvement for both FW provisioning times and WF success rate.
